WEBVTT

00:34.409 --> 00:36.786
In all the decisions I have made
           in my public life,

00:37.662 --> 00:40.498
I have always tried to do
     what was best for the nation.

00:41.499 --> 00:45.045
In the past few days, however,
      it has become evident to me

00:45.879 --> 00:48.798
that I no longer have
     a strong enough political base

00:49.507 --> 00:53.803
in the Congress to justify
        continuing that effort.

00:55.180 --> 00:58.433
Therefore, I shall resign
             the presidency

00:58.892 --> 01:00.393
effective at noon tomorrow.

01:01.728 --> 01:05.732
Vice President Ford
     will be sworn in as president

01:06.232 --> 01:08.777
at that hour in this office.

01:10.236 --> 01:12.280
As I recall
       the high hopes for America

01:13.114 --> 01:15.241
with which we began
           this second term,

01:16.076 --> 01:17.327
I feel a great sadness

01:18.745 --> 01:21.456
that I will not be here
      in this office working on...

01:26.795 --> 01:28.338
Mr. and Mrs. Ford
         have joined the Nixons

01:29.255 --> 01:33.510
as they make the last walk out
      to Army One, the helicopter.

01:33.802 --> 01:34.761
Congratulations.

01:35.470 --> 01:37.388
-Congratulations or condolences?

01:38.306 --> 01:41.142
She's all yours.
              Be safe.

01:43.603 --> 01:45.480
There is the
       President waving goodbye.

01:45.939 --> 01:47.398
Can you hear the applause?

01:52.112 --> 01:54.531
President Nixon's helicopter
        going over the fountains

01:55.115 --> 01:56.157
of the White House south lawn.

01:56.950 --> 02:00.245
I am acutely aware
      that you have not elected me

02:00.829 --> 02:03.706
as your president
          by your ballots,

02:04.415 --> 02:09.170
so I ask you to confirm me as
           your president

02:09.963 --> 02:11.214
with your prayers.

02:11.840 --> 02:15.426
I have not campaigned either
         for the presidency

02:15.802 --> 02:16.719
or the vice presidency.

02:17.345 --> 02:22.350
I am indebted to no man
       and only to one woman,

02:23.184 --> 02:24.477
my dear wife...

02:27.647 --> 02:30.275
...as I begin
      this very difficult job.

02:31.860 --> 02:36.197
I have not sought
    this enormous responsibility,

02:37.657 --> 02:39.200
but I will not shirk it.

02:40.160 --> 02:42.453
This land is your land

02:44.873 --> 02:47.333
This land is my land

02:50.336 --> 02:53.173
From California

02:54.174 --> 02:58.344
Well to the New York Island

02:59.345 --> 03:02.891
From the Redwood Forest

03:04.309 --> 03:08.396
To the Gulf Stream Waters

03:09.355 --> 03:13.234
I tell you this land

03:13.818 --> 03:17.488
Was made for you and me

03:17.697 --> 03:19.199
Yeah

03:19.866 --> 03:23.244
Mmm

03:24.037 --> 03:27.957
One bright sunny morning

03:28.583 --> 03:32.545
Well, in the shadow
             of a steeple

03:33.421 --> 03:37.842
Down by the welfare office

03:38.384 --> 03:42.305
I saw my people

03:43.264 --> 03:47.310
I was wondering if this land

03:47.894 --> 03:53.274
Was made for you and me

03:56.945 --> 03:58.947
-Yes, push!

03:59.447 --> 04:01.241
One, two. One, two. One, two.

04:01.741 --> 04:03.618
Come on! One, two. Push!

04:06.579 --> 04:08.998
Come on. Push through.
             Five more.

04:09.582 --> 04:10.583
Hard as you can. You got this.

04:10.959 --> 04:12.460
Don't stop. Come on.

04:12.752 --> 04:15.129
Come on. Come on.

04:15.588 --> 04:16.798
Four! Five!

04:18.758 --> 04:20.969
Senator Hillary Clinton
      has opened up a huge lead

04:21.552 --> 04:22.345
over her democratic challengers

04:23.263 --> 04:24.597
according to a new
     Washington Post ABC News   poll.

04:25.473 --> 04:27.308
Senator Hillary Clinton
   is still the Democrat to beat.

04:28.268 --> 04:31.145
The poll shows support for both
     Barack Obama and John Edwards

04:31.604 --> 04:32.647
is dropping off.

04:42.407 --> 04:45.159
Can't say I've taken
             that route.

04:45.660 --> 04:47.537
Safest way, ma'am.

04:47.829 --> 04:49.289
Great.

04:50.498 --> 04:52.333
I know. Packed.

04:54.294 --> 04:56.337
Mmm. And you're finally on time.

04:56.963 --> 04:58.756
Well, you know,
       I didn't wanna miss out

04:59.340 --> 05:00.633
on some one-on-one time
              with you.

05:01.592 --> 05:04.053
Yeah, we can't miss
      our date night tradition,

05:04.679 --> 05:06.806
even if we have to shut
        the whole place down.

05:07.432 --> 05:08.599
-Oh, yeah. Thank you.
             -Thank you.

05:09.475 --> 05:10.893
You may not have to worry
        about it much longer.

05:11.519 --> 05:14.981
I-- I'm still trailing Hillary
          by double digits.

05:15.606 --> 05:19.360
Yeah, well, she seems to really
              want it.

05:19.986 --> 05:24.324
Yeah, she's whopping my ass
          in every debate.

05:24.782 --> 05:25.992
Sorry.

05:27.785 --> 05:31.998
You know, my-- my team thinks
             that I have

05:32.540 --> 05:34.292
-a relatability issue.
              -Mm-hmm.

05:35.001 --> 05:39.172
But they've got this idea
     on how to ameliorate that.

05:39.839 --> 05:41.966
Is it to stop you
      from casually using words

05:42.550 --> 05:44.844
like relatability
           and ameliorate?

05:46.512 --> 05:47.722
Actually, it's you.

05:48.181 --> 05:50.266
-All right. Look,

05:50.725 --> 05:51.934
you're stunning.

05:52.518 --> 05:53.936
-No, you are, and you're--
                -Ugh.

05:54.520 --> 05:57.273
You're brilliant and relatable--

05:57.899 --> 05:59.192
I don't know,
     it's the best word for it.

05:59.901 --> 06:02.904
You are relatable and certainly
        more relatable than--

06:03.529 --> 06:05.073
I don't know,
      some half-Kenyan brother

06:05.573 --> 06:06.908
from fucking Hawaii, you know?

06:07.533 --> 06:10.536
Okay, then what does
         all of this entail?

06:11.913 --> 06:13.373
Well...

06:14.540 --> 06:15.875
-a few speaking engagements--

06:16.501 --> 06:17.502
-No, no, listen. But we'll--
             -Barack...

06:18.544 --> 06:20.421
We'll work the schedule around
 the kids. It'll be family first.

06:20.922 --> 06:22.215
I don't know, you know?

06:22.882 --> 06:24.384
And you know I don't love
          public speaking.

06:25.009 --> 06:28.679
I get it,
   but you're an amazing speaker.

06:29.055 --> 06:31.557
And it'd be a chance

06:32.392 --> 06:34.852
for us to work together
             as a team.

06:36.437 --> 06:37.897
And I miss you.

06:39.107 --> 06:41.401
There you go
      with that sweet talking.

06:44.529 --> 06:46.406
So you'll think about it?

06:48.116 --> 06:49.617
I'll think about it.

06:50.743 --> 06:51.244
All right.

06:53.454 --> 06:54.205
-I'll take that as a win.
             -Thank you.

06:54.914 --> 06:57.250
After you give me dessert,
        I'll think about it.

06:57.917 --> 07:00.711
-Oh, you're gonna get dessert.
               -Yeah.

07:01.587 --> 07:04.006
No one knows more about
      the character, the heart

07:04.549 --> 07:06.092
or the intention of Barack Obama

07:06.801 --> 07:09.303
than the woman who agreed
   to take this journey with him.

07:09.929 --> 07:12.223
She's gonna make some
         kind of tremendous

07:12.807 --> 07:15.101
-First Lady of this nation.

07:15.643 --> 07:17.311
Ladies and gentlemen,
           Michelle Obama!

07:18.104 --> 07:22.150
The next First Lady of the
   United States, Michelle Obama.

07:22.775 --> 07:24.152
We got to make this land
            a better land

07:24.777 --> 07:26.487
Than the world
           in which we live

07:27.280 --> 07:29.323
And we got to help each man
           Be a better man

07:29.949 --> 07:33.369
With the kindness
             that we give

07:34.078 --> 07:38.583
I feel privileged to be a part
      of even witnessing this.

07:39.459 --> 07:40.918
Traveling around states

07:41.502 --> 07:43.546
and being reminded
          that there's more

07:44.130 --> 07:45.840
that unites us than divides us.

07:46.799 --> 07:49.302
-   I know we can make it
         -   I know we can

07:49.969 --> 07:51.596
I know darn well
       That we can work it out

07:52.638 --> 07:55.600
Yes we can, I know we can can
 Yes we can can, why can't we?

07:56.184 --> 07:57.560
If you wanna yes we can can

07:58.144 --> 07:59.729
I know we can make it work

08:00.521 --> 08:03.816
I know we can make it
              if we try

08:04.859 --> 08:06.486
Thank you.

08:08.112 --> 08:09.071
Thank you so much.

08:09.614 --> 08:11.491
We love you,
              Michelle!

08:11.949 --> 08:12.867
Thank you.

08:13.868 --> 08:16.370
I am honored and excited
             to be here.

08:16.996 --> 08:19.165
This has been an amazing year
               for us.

08:19.790 --> 08:22.210
Just think where we were
            one year ago.

08:23.002 --> 08:27.131
Barack was standing in front
 of the State Capitol in Illinois

08:27.840 --> 08:30.551
to announce that he was running
           for president.

08:34.847 --> 08:37.767
What we have learned
           over this year

08:38.684 --> 08:40.937
is that hope
        is making a comeback.

08:41.521 --> 08:42.355
And let me tell you something,

08:42.980 --> 08:46.943
for the first time
        in my adult lifetime,

08:47.527 --> 08:49.362
I am really proud of my country.

08:50.196 --> 08:52.532
-   I know we can make it
       -   I know that we can

08:53.533 --> 08:56.869
I know darn well that we can
     Work it out, work it out...

09:00.706 --> 09:02.750
Thank you! Thank you!

09:04.210 --> 09:07.463
I know darn well that we can
       Work it out, work it out

09:12.093 --> 09:13.761
-   I know we can make it
       -   I know that we can

09:14.720 --> 09:16.180
I know darn well that we can
       Work it out, work it out

09:16.847 --> 09:18.558
There's so many needy
             So many poor

09:19.267 --> 09:22.603
But love and understanding
        Is the key to the door

09:26.774 --> 09:27.733
We better get going.

09:28.943 --> 09:31.654
-Mel?
       -Fucking racist fucks.

09:32.238 --> 09:33.990
-What's going on?
               -Sorry.

09:34.865 --> 09:35.950
They-- They twisted your words.

09:36.909 --> 09:38.202
-What? What?
   -They twisted your words.

09:38.911 --> 09:42.290
"I'm proud of my country
        for the first time."

09:43.791 --> 09:47.628
Shit.
     "I never loved my country."

09:48.087 --> 09:49.213
Right.

09:49.797 --> 09:50.756
-Okay.
    -Come on. Let's keep moving.

09:51.591 --> 09:52.341
Now that her husband

09:52.967 --> 09:54.176
is the Democrats'
          presumptive nominee,

09:54.802 --> 09:56.596
Michelle Obama is expected
             to come under

09:57.221 --> 09:58.764
ever greater scrutiny
            from the media.

09:59.640 --> 10:01.309
She's always angry every time
       she gets on television.

10:02.101 --> 10:05.271
I think the American people
   deserve a thorough examination

10:05.771 --> 10:06.397
of everything about her.

10:06.981 --> 10:08.983
The angry Black woman
             First Lady?

10:32.006 --> 10:32.715
Ready?

10:33.341 --> 10:34.592
Ma'am, we believe it's best
          you take the car.

10:35.176 --> 10:36.761
I wanna walk my girls
          to school today.

10:37.637 --> 10:39.388
It's a beautiful morning,
      and we need the fresh air

10:40.014 --> 10:41.349
and a break from all of this.
            Right, girls?

10:41.974 --> 10:43.476
-Yes.

10:44.852 --> 10:45.811
-Michelle!

10:46.771 --> 10:48.439
Michelle, do you
 have any terrorist affiliations?

10:48.981 --> 10:50.441
Do you hate America
            or Americans?

10:51.108 --> 10:53.152
Why are you not
      proud to be an American?

10:55.321 --> 10:56.739
What do you think about your
     father running for office?

10:57.657 --> 10:59.241
How is the campaign
 impacting your children's lives?

10:59.867 --> 11:01.327
Just one more
         question. Did any--

11:03.704 --> 11:08.501
I will not respond
           to these lies,

11:09.877 --> 11:14.090
nor will I stand for you
 bringing my girls into all this.

11:14.674 --> 11:16.133
That's what we're not gonna do.

11:16.676 --> 11:19.679
But I will say this.

11:20.304 --> 11:23.641
I am genuinely proud
        of all the excitement

11:24.225 --> 11:26.936
building around
         Barack's campaign.

11:27.353 --> 11:28.854
It makes me hopeful.

11:29.855 --> 11:34.318
People of all shades and--
              and ages

11:34.902 --> 11:39.407
and-- and creeds
        all working together.

11:40.700 --> 11:41.409
Now, if you don't mind,

11:42.034 --> 11:44.870
I'm gonna walk my daughters
             to school.

11:47.707 --> 11:49.041
Come on, girls.

12:21.282 --> 12:21.991
Why, thank you.

12:22.867 --> 12:24.076
-Ma'am.
       -Mrs. Roosevelt.

12:24.243 --> 12:25.286
Earl!

12:25.911 --> 12:26.704
I'll be escorting you
         to the White House.

12:27.413 --> 12:31.751
Yes, I think I'm going to take
            the long way.

12:32.543 --> 12:33.753
Clear the cobwebs.

12:34.253 --> 12:35.379
Don't ask.

12:36.088 --> 12:37.173
Mrs. Roosevelt, ma'am,

12:38.132 --> 12:39.800
I must insist you get in the
   car. It's for your own safety.

12:40.468 --> 12:43.637
No one wants to hurt me.
      I'm not important enough.

12:44.263 --> 12:45.347
Oh, I don't know,
               Mrs. R.

12:45.973 --> 12:48.809
I might hurt you
    if you keep it up like this.

12:52.813 --> 12:56.817
Oh. Oh, that's wonderful.

12:59.320 --> 13:01.113
Hello. What's your name?

13:01.489 --> 13:03.115
-I'm Eleanor.
              -Oh, no.

13:03.324 --> 13:04.116
You're, uh--

13:04.617 --> 13:05.618
Eleanor. Eleanor Roosevelt.

13:06.243 --> 13:09.079
So nice to meet you.
          What's your name?

13:09.246 --> 13:10.039
John.

13:10.831 --> 13:11.707
-Hello, John.
    -Mrs. R., we should really--

13:12.500 --> 13:15.211
That is one hardy
   handshake. What work do you do?

13:15.795 --> 13:18.964
I don't do any work. I'm busted.

13:19.173 --> 13:19.882
Of course.

13:20.508 --> 13:24.428
I'm-- I'm so sorry.
        What work did you do?

13:25.137 --> 13:27.515
I forged steel.
   Built skyscrapers in New York.

13:28.140 --> 13:31.227
Oh,
       what a wonderful skill.

13:31.977 --> 13:33.354
You must be so proud.

13:34.355 --> 13:37.817
Well, you're a part of history,
                John.

13:38.359 --> 13:40.194
Such a pleasure to meet you.

13:41.278 --> 13:42.154
And you, all of you.

13:43.113 --> 13:44.615
-Thank you so much. Thank you.
         -Thank you, ma'am.

13:45.199 --> 13:46.575
Oh, I do like your hat.

13:47.201 --> 13:49.870
-Oh, that's very nice.
      -Thank you though!

13:59.463 --> 14:00.673
-There you are.
        -So sorry.

14:01.215 --> 14:02.716
I feared you weren't coming.

14:04.009 --> 14:05.803
Well, it's a pleasure
        to see you, Eleanor.

14:06.387 --> 14:08.722
And you too, Lou.
       Shall we make a start?

14:09.390 --> 14:11.225
I thought we'd have tea
        and a light breakfast

14:11.684 --> 14:12.601
before I give you the tour.

14:13.185 --> 14:16.063
Of course. That would be lovely.

14:21.360 --> 14:24.989
I'm sure you're excited
 to begin the decorating process.

14:25.906 --> 14:28.576
Oh, yes.
    Mrs. Roosevelt certainly is.

14:29.201 --> 14:31.912
You can't go wrong
       with an oriental silk.

14:32.413 --> 14:34.498
No, you most certainly cannot.

14:35.040 --> 14:35.583
Sorry.

14:36.166 --> 14:39.086
And this is the master bedroom.

14:43.173 --> 14:45.885
That door over there
       is your dressing room.

14:46.385 --> 14:47.261
I used it as my study,

14:48.220 --> 14:51.891
but they always called it
    the dressing room regardless.

14:53.225 --> 14:56.061
The Wilsons used it
      as a private dining room.

15:05.571 --> 15:07.281
What on Earth?

15:18.125 --> 15:21.170
Nine presidents
     brought their slaves here.

15:21.629 --> 15:23.339
I never knew...

15:24.298 --> 15:27.343
It wasn't recorded how many
    of them required their slaves

15:27.927 --> 15:30.596
to have access
         to their bedrooms.

15:40.272 --> 15:41.273
Well, I hope you're
           making me sound

15:41.774 --> 15:43.442
interesting and intelligent.

15:44.068 --> 15:47.321
-And possibly even fascinating.
                -Oh!

15:48.113 --> 15:49.657
I'll do what I can.

15:52.743 --> 15:53.577
Can I ask you something

15:54.119 --> 15:56.455
-Of course. Always.
          -off the record?

15:57.581 --> 16:02.294
How do you really feel
       about being First Lady?

16:03.587 --> 16:05.005
Oh.

16:06.632 --> 16:08.092
Well...

16:09.301 --> 16:11.720
I'm not thrilled about the fact

16:12.429 --> 16:17.226
that my title refers to my sex
       rather than my skills.

16:17.518 --> 16:19.061
-Yeah.
                -Mmm.

16:19.979 --> 16:23.315
Does sound like a crude term
 a man might use for his ex-wife.

16:27.027 --> 16:29.780
And it's recently been made
          very clear to me

16:30.489 --> 16:34.743
that I'm to smile, nod,
   and gaze adoringly at Franklin

16:35.452 --> 16:38.414
every time we happen to be
     in the same room together.

16:38.539 --> 16:40.416
Mmm...

16:41.000 --> 16:42.501
Well, what does that look like?

16:42.835 --> 16:45.462
Oh. Well...

16:46.797 --> 16:49.299
That's awful.

16:54.346 --> 16:56.181
Oh, that's my daughter Anna.

16:57.016 --> 16:59.059
She's just gone through
             a divorce.

17:00.019 --> 17:01.478
Off the record.

17:02.354 --> 17:03.689
It was the right thing to do,

17:04.231 --> 17:07.693
but her grandmother
           is apoplectic.

17:08.235 --> 17:11.363
So, she's a Progressive
              like you?

17:11.739 --> 17:15.075
Yes, I suppose she is.

17:16.035 --> 17:18.037
Good for her.

17:19.538 --> 17:20.748
Well, thank you, Hick.

17:21.707 --> 17:25.335
Always. Now get to it.

17:30.591 --> 17:31.592
Hello!

17:32.217 --> 17:34.011
-Hello, darling. How are you?
             -I'm good.

17:34.553 --> 17:36.180
Sis, come say hello.

17:37.931 --> 17:38.891
Little Anna. 

17:39.391 --> 17:40.642
Oh, Louis. 

17:41.101 --> 17:42.269
Look who's growing.

17:43.103 --> 17:43.812
How is the speech coming along?

17:44.396 --> 17:45.439
The President would like
           your thoughts.

17:46.398 --> 17:48.317
Well, Sis and I are going to
   grab sundaes at the restaurant.

17:49.234 --> 17:52.863
We were wondering if you could
   come but seems like a busy one.

17:53.363 --> 17:54.281
Oh, it's a busy one.

17:55.115 --> 17:56.366
Well, you'll have to get a scoop
               on me.

17:57.242 --> 17:58.577
All right, more for us.
        Let's go, chickadee.

17:59.078 --> 18:01.413
-Have fun.
             -Bye. Bye.

18:03.082 --> 18:05.125
He asked for me himself?

18:05.542 --> 18:06.752
Almost.

18:07.795 --> 18:09.588
All right.

18:30.818 --> 18:32.152
Hello, Missus.

18:36.406 --> 18:38.826
Have you been calling?
       I was out for meetings.

18:39.326 --> 18:41.495
No, no. I've been wrapped up.

18:43.288 --> 18:45.165
What do you have so far?

18:47.501 --> 18:48.669
A slippery fish.

18:48.961 --> 18:51.255
Mm-mmm. May I?

18:51.964 --> 18:53.841
No, it's not ready yet.

18:56.343 --> 18:58.887
Is it true that I am not to have

18:59.471 --> 19:01.682
a proper job
       in your administration?

19:02.266 --> 19:03.600
Will you stop listening
              to Louis?

19:04.184 --> 19:06.270
Well, give me something else
              to hear.

19:06.520 --> 19:07.646
Fine.

19:11.358 --> 19:13.318
I am not entirely comfortable.

19:14.153 --> 19:15.654
Nobody else is getting
          two appointments.

19:16.196 --> 19:18.866
I'm not asking
        for two appointments.

19:23.328 --> 19:23.912
I'll think about it.

19:24.496 --> 19:25.873
Don't push me off, Franklin.

19:26.540 --> 19:30.377
I am your wife,
    not one of your girlfriends.

19:36.884 --> 19:37.926
And I need to work.

19:38.468 --> 19:39.386
-You know that.

19:40.179 --> 19:41.680
You have made yourself
          abundantly clear.

19:42.306 --> 19:45.184
-You will work.

19:45.684 --> 19:46.560
What is it?

19:48.020 --> 19:50.898
Sir, if you're not busy, we'd
   better get back to the speech.

19:51.690 --> 19:54.109
Not busy at all, boys.
   Come on. Let's get back to it.

19:54.735 --> 19:57.738
Let's start with this wording
             right here.

19:58.405 --> 19:59.990
"Attempts by
     the previous administration

20:00.574 --> 20:02.826
were lost on tired
         and old tradition,

20:03.243 --> 20:04.036
leaving you fearful."

20:04.703 --> 20:06.205
Now, I like the idea of that,
           the sentiment,

20:06.705 --> 20:08.081
but it's lacking punch.

20:08.582 --> 20:10.709
It-- It feels passive this way.

20:29.436 --> 20:33.607
Oh, yeah.

20:41.531 --> 20:43.909
Could someone please
       come collect something

20:44.576 --> 20:46.954
and take it
       to the president-elect?

20:52.459 --> 20:55.754
"Nothing is so much
           to be feared...

20:57.256 --> 20:58.590
as fear".

21:05.264 --> 21:08.725
I am certain
   that my fellow Americans expect

21:09.101 --> 21:10.018
that on my induction,

21:10.644 --> 21:13.021
this is preeminently the time
         to speak the truth.

21:13.605 --> 21:16.817
The whole truth,
         frankly and boldly.

21:17.442 --> 21:18.402
Nor need we shrink

21:19.278 --> 21:23.240
from honestly facing conditions
        in our country today.

21:23.949 --> 21:27.911
This great nation will endure
         as it has endured.

21:28.787 --> 21:31.581
We'll revive and we'll prosper.

21:41.300 --> 21:43.010
So, first of all,

21:44.136 --> 21:46.138
let me assert my firm belief

21:46.847 --> 21:50.934
that the only thing we have
       to fear is fear itself.

21:51.518 --> 21:54.813
--Oh, yes.

21:58.817 --> 22:01.403
May God protect each
        and every one of you

22:01.945 --> 22:04.156
and guide me in the coming days.

22:04.531 --> 22:05.032
Thank you.

22:05.615 --> 22:07.784
--Come.

22:10.329 --> 22:13.790
Oh, that was a very
     powerful speech, wasn't it?

22:14.333 --> 22:15.208
Mmm, yes, it was brilliant.

22:16.001 --> 22:20.088
Yes, Franklin always knows
    just the right thing to say.

22:20.672 --> 22:22.049
It's one of his many gifts.

22:22.674 --> 22:24.092
One of the great pleasures
             of marriage

22:24.718 --> 22:27.387
is savoring your husband's
           finest moments.

22:28.013 --> 22:30.098
Second only to savoring that
            of your sons.

22:30.557 --> 22:31.850
Thank you!

22:32.809 --> 22:34.061
Yes.

22:35.854 --> 22:38.899
I don't believe I've
             ever smiled

22:39.399 --> 22:41.735
for so many hours in a row.

22:45.405 --> 22:48.950
I do think they should
           issue warnings.

22:49.576 --> 22:53.080
Inauguration festivities
       may cause frozen face.

22:55.665 --> 22:58.752
Is it stuck? Am I doomed
       to be a grinning fool?

22:59.711 --> 23:03.423
You are the farthest thing
   from a fool I have ever known.

23:05.759 --> 23:08.929
I think your speech went over
        very well, Franklin.

23:09.554 --> 23:11.765
-Thanks to you.
        -Oh, don't be silly.

23:13.725 --> 23:18.397
You really are so good
    at conveying hope, you know.

23:20.023 --> 23:22.234
You think you've always
           been that way?

23:23.068 --> 23:26.905
My mother says even as a child
     I had a soothing presence.

23:27.406 --> 23:28.365
Oh, soothing is one thing.

23:29.241 --> 23:33.328
It's quite another to lead a
 country out of its darkest hour.

23:34.204 --> 23:37.124
Well, you were instrumental
   in helping crafting my message.

23:37.624 --> 23:39.751
So I'm grateful for you.

23:41.086 --> 23:42.921
We make a good team.

23:45.757 --> 23:46.925
Yes, we do.

23:50.137 --> 23:51.638
Should we go to bed?

23:52.973 --> 23:57.769
Oh, I cannot think of anything
        I'd like to do more.

24:01.481 --> 24:04.568
-Good night, Franklin.

24:05.485 --> 24:07.946
Sweet dreams.

24:09.156 --> 24:13.785
Congratulations! You so
        deserve it. 

24:14.953 --> 24:15.912
Here we are!

24:16.288 --> 24:18.665
Yes. Here we are indeed.

24:19.499 --> 24:20.208
Oh! Hello.
          What's your name?

24:20.792 --> 24:23.003
-Charles.
       -Charles, I'm Eleanor.

24:23.670 --> 24:25.881
I'll be seeing quite a lot
           of you I think.

24:30.093 --> 24:31.553
More champagne, sir?

24:32.971 --> 24:35.724
I think we should move over
     to the whiskey. Don't you?

24:36.016 --> 24:37.476
Very well, sir.

25:11.843 --> 25:13.220
Bob, a lot has been written
             about the fact

25:13.845 --> 25:15.639
that president-elect Obama
               is looking

25:16.640 --> 25:21.061
into ways to reverse various
     Bush administration policies.

25:21.728 --> 25:23.522
Is there danger
       in doing that too quickly?

25:24.147 --> 25:25.732
-They're asleep.

25:27.067 --> 25:30.153
Oh. I don't wanna keep
          missing bedtime.

25:30.862 --> 25:32.155
-   ...these are things the, uh,
          -Mmm.

25:32.822 --> 25:35.200
president has, uh, done
          by executive order,

25:35.825 --> 25:37.077
and they can be, uh,
             easily undone.

25:37.744 --> 25:39.162
I think that's some
             of the first--

25:42.541 --> 25:45.377
In four years, I don't want
       to look back and think,

25:46.586 --> 25:49.839
"What did I become
       living in that house?"

25:51.758 --> 25:55.428
Well, you know,
      in-- in eight years, uh,

25:56.096 --> 26:00.016
I think you are still gonna be
         that bougie lawyer

26:00.559 --> 26:02.185
with that Audi 

26:02.894 --> 26:05.897
and that fucking attitude
      that I fell in love with.

26:09.067 --> 26:13.280
-South Side forever! 
       -That's right. Mm-hmm.

26:13.780 --> 26:17.742
Mmm. We need a road map, Barack.

26:18.577 --> 26:19.661
I will not miss the girls
             growing up.

26:20.287 --> 26:24.040
Mmm, no. Me neither.
      We won't let that happen.

26:24.624 --> 26:26.710
-Mm-hmm.
     -All right? I promise you.

26:27.085 --> 26:28.044
Mmm.

26:28.628 --> 26:31.298
You are gonna be
         a dope First Lady.

26:31.881 --> 26:35.135
Michelle Obama née Robinson

26:35.719 --> 26:38.054
has never failed a test.

26:38.638 --> 26:39.556
-You're right.
           -That's right.

26:40.223 --> 26:42.642
-I got this. 
    -Yeah, you do. Shake it girl!

26:43.602 --> 26:46.479
What I don't got is all those
    clothes you got on the floor,

26:47.105 --> 26:49.983
Barack Obama,
    President of the United Sta--

26:50.942 --> 26:52.944
-Pick up your clothes!
   -I got it. I got it. I got you.

26:53.153 --> 26:54.195
Mm-hmm.

26:54.654 --> 26:55.572
Mmm.

26:56.114 --> 26:56.823
I got this.

26:57.657 --> 26:59.159
-Clothes all over.

26:59.826 --> 27:00.535
I should really have somebody
             to help me

27:01.161 --> 27:02.537
-tidy this thing up, right?
          -Mmm.

27:03.121 --> 27:05.206
I got nuclear codes
           to think about.

27:05.332 --> 27:06.833
Mmm.

27:14.924 --> 27:15.467
You okay?

27:16.134 --> 27:18.428
-How do we feel about Gwen?

27:18.970 --> 27:21.181
-Morning, Gwen. Hi.
             -Hi, Gwen.

27:21.806 --> 27:24.017
--Madam First Lady.

27:28.313 --> 27:29.397
We're already behind schedule.

27:30.148 --> 27:32.400
I had to drop the girls off
   for their first day at school.

27:32.984 --> 27:34.277
Oh!
       I thought Mrs. Robinson

27:34.861 --> 27:35.570
and Secret Service
         were handling that.

27:36.279 --> 27:38.156
My daughters are not a matter
           to be handled.

27:38.782 --> 27:40.325
I had to ensure
        that they settled in.

27:40.700 --> 27:41.493
Of course.

27:42.118 --> 27:44.037
So, we want to hit
         the ground running.

27:44.496 --> 27:45.372
And with Rahm's approval,

27:46.122 --> 27:48.041
my team and I have come up
     with several ideas for you.

27:48.375 --> 27:50.377
Rahm has approved...

27:51.211 --> 27:53.004
Okay. Let me hear 'em.

27:54.839 --> 27:59.219
He feels, and we all feel, that
    a White House garden project

27:59.719 --> 28:00.845
could be a great opportunity

28:01.680 --> 28:03.848
for people to see a new side
               of you.

28:05.725 --> 28:06.935
The First Lady tending
             the garden,

28:07.852 --> 28:10.397
growing fruits and vegetables
          with local kids.

28:11.064 --> 28:12.607
Great photo ops.

28:13.024 --> 28:13.525
Good news, team.

28:14.150 --> 28:15.193
The men in the West Wing
            have given us

28:15.735 --> 28:17.237
the green light
       to plant some carrots.

28:19.072 --> 28:20.365
Uh, that's not--
      that's not what I meant.

28:21.032 --> 28:23.201
Um, all right.
     This, uh, this is for you.

28:25.161 --> 28:26.663
Mrs. Ford won't be able
     to attend the inauguration.

28:27.372 --> 28:30.208
She's almost 90,
   but she wanted to write to you.

28:30.709 --> 28:32.919
Betty Ford wrote me a letter.

28:33.336 --> 28:34.212
Wow.

28:36.214 --> 28:37.674
We have a fitting
     for your inauguration gown.

28:38.383 --> 28:41.720
And this is great,
      Vogue   has offered a feature

28:42.345 --> 28:44.389
with Annie Leibovitz
         to shoot the cover.

28:44.848 --> 28:45.682
Amazing, right?

28:46.391 --> 28:50.103
Sure. Excellent opportunity
      to talk about rutabagas.

28:52.731 --> 28:53.523
What's a rutabaga?

28:54.232 --> 28:56.234
-A turnip, I believe.
     -Come on, Gwen.

28:56.776 --> 28:57.402
I spoke throughout the campaign

28:57.944 --> 28:58.903
about civic duty,
         unemployment and--

28:59.863 --> 29:02.574
And you were incredible. And
    now we're in the White House.

29:03.199 --> 29:05.201
And the team
    in the West Wing wanna shape

29:05.785 --> 29:06.494
and help you grow
         into your new role.

29:07.203 --> 29:09.372
I'm a lawyer
    and an expert in health care.

29:10.081 --> 29:11.624
They wanna turn me
    into a Black Martha Stewart?

29:12.292 --> 29:14.335
I meant no disrespect,
        but Rahm feels that--

29:14.919 --> 29:16.546
You know, I'm looking forward

29:17.130 --> 29:18.506
to hearing all about
          Rahm's feelings,

29:19.090 --> 29:19.924
so why don't you let him know

29:20.759 --> 29:21.843
that I would like some time
              with him.

29:22.469 --> 29:26.473
-I'll do that.
            -Okay. Okay.

29:28.391 --> 29:31.853
We have a very important meeting
 coming up next Tuesday that is--

29:32.437 --> 29:33.480
Dear Mrs. Obama,

29:34.105 --> 29:37.484
you probably feel
         so overwhelmed today.

29:38.109 --> 29:41.279
You can't imagine how unprepared
                I felt.

29:41.780 --> 29:43.490
But the job will find you.

29:43.990 --> 29:45.617
It has a way of doing that.

29:46.284 --> 29:48.453
You are forever a part
             of history now

29:49.078 --> 29:51.581
but will always be
             one of a kind.

29:52.457 --> 29:54.709
Today, you'll probably feel
 like you have nothing in common

29:55.502 --> 29:58.588
with all of the women who
     were First Ladies before you.

29:59.255 --> 30:02.634
Trust me when I say
         we all felt that way.

30:03.176 --> 30:04.928
Gonna miss this place.

30:13.978 --> 30:15.230
We'll have fun in our new house.

30:15.438 --> 30:16.439
Mm-hmm.

30:17.023 --> 30:17.899
Sleeping in our
         separate bedrooms,

30:18.525 --> 30:21.861
like a proper presidential
        husband and his wife.

30:22.445 --> 30:23.404
That's not happening.

30:23.863 --> 30:24.697
Better not be.

30:25.323 --> 30:27.408
Though, after this week,
       I might change my mind.

30:27.826 --> 30:29.285
Don't you dare.

30:31.454 --> 30:34.123
You're gonna make
       a terrific First Lady.

30:46.886 --> 30:48.680
Ford residence. This is Betty.

30:49.180 --> 30:50.139
Madam First Lady?

30:51.057 --> 30:55.311
No, uh-- Y-Yes, yes. I mean,
        that's me. 

30:56.187 --> 30:57.730
My name is Debbie Winthrop.

30:58.356 --> 31:00.900
I was Mrs. Nixon's
          social secretary.

31:01.484 --> 31:03.695
Of course. Yes, I remember you.

31:04.237 --> 31:06.281
We were wondering
        what you wanted to do

31:06.739 --> 31:08.575
for the upcoming State Dinner.

31:09.158 --> 31:09.909
The what?

31:10.869 --> 31:14.998
Uh, King Hussein of Jordan
   is coming in four days, ma'am.

31:17.375 --> 31:20.587
I see. I see.

31:21.212 --> 31:24.299
And the idea is he'll want
          something to eat

31:24.757 --> 31:26.885
after that long trip. 

31:27.719 --> 31:29.053
And the queen, ma'am.

31:30.555 --> 31:32.056
Of course.

31:33.892 --> 31:35.602
Uh, well...

31:37.061 --> 31:38.688
I wish someone would've told me
             about this.

31:39.397 --> 31:43.610
We told Pat Nixon, ma'am.
       The former First Lady.

31:44.110 --> 31:46.112
Yes, I know who Pat Nixon is.

31:46.529 --> 31:47.280
Of course.

31:47.739 --> 31:48.531
Let me give it some thought,

31:49.115 --> 31:52.160
and I'll get back to you
          as soon as I can.

31:53.202 --> 31:54.746
Okay.
     Thank you very much, ma'am.

31:55.246 --> 31:57.790
Okay. Thank you for calling.

31:58.249 --> 31:59.292
Goodbye.

32:09.218 --> 32:10.970
I'll move into the White House.

32:11.471 --> 32:13.389
I'll do the best I can.

32:14.599 --> 32:18.519
And if they don't like it,
       then they can kick me out,

32:19.145 --> 32:21.397
but they can't make me somebody
                I'm not.

32:26.235 --> 32:27.737
She's totally unsuited
            for the role.

32:28.321 --> 32:30.615
Well, she seems very confident
               to me.

32:31.115 --> 32:32.283
That's the problem.

32:33.284 --> 32:34.243
I don't wanna get into details,
              but, um,

32:35.119 --> 32:36.788
she's had her fair share
       of personal struggles.

32:37.330 --> 32:38.414
We all know the lights in here,

32:39.332 --> 32:41.042
they tend to flush that sort of
   thing right out into the open,

32:41.584 --> 32:42.669
so that's where you come in.

32:43.461 --> 32:47.298
We want you to stay on. Keep the
     East Wing running smoothly.

32:47.757 --> 32:48.758
Of course. That's my job.

32:49.634 --> 32:51.386
But we're counting on
 you to guide the First Lady into

32:52.303 --> 32:55.807
taking a more reserved Pat-
   Nixon-type approach to things.

32:56.349 --> 32:58.267
Oh, show her the art of facade.

32:58.643 --> 32:59.811
Encourage discretion.

33:01.020 --> 33:03.773
Have you met the First Lady?

33:04.482 --> 33:07.610
You can start by limiting,
        preferably canceling,

33:08.194 --> 33:09.487
any upcoming events
           and gatherings,

33:10.029 --> 33:10.738
starting with the State Dinner.

33:11.364 --> 33:12.532
Well, I already told her
         that was happening.

33:13.157 --> 33:14.534
We have a meeting about it,
            uh, shortly.

33:15.201 --> 33:17.662
I know you can steer her
         towards canceling.

33:18.371 --> 33:19.163
And if I can't?

33:20.039 --> 33:23.209
We're confident. You can
    convince her woman-to-woman.

33:25.211 --> 33:29.674
You know, Mrs. Ford's
       good nature and candor

33:30.383 --> 33:32.719
might be just the thing
 the White House needs right now.

33:33.302 --> 33:34.178
She really seems quite capable.

33:34.721 --> 33:36.055
Debbie.
     I know that you understand

33:36.639 --> 33:37.598
how vitally important it is

33:38.224 --> 33:39.892
that this party hold the reigns
          of this country.

33:40.518 --> 33:41.477
In less than two years,
           the president's

33:42.061 --> 33:42.937
gonna have to run
           for his office.

33:43.563 --> 33:46.024
And so, the smaller
      that Mrs. Ford's role is

33:46.733 --> 33:50.319
and the less that we hear
   about her thoughts, opinions--

33:50.695 --> 33:53.364
The less noise she makes.

33:54.365 --> 33:55.408
Thank you.

33:58.536 --> 33:59.871
-Madam First Lady.
           -Good morning.

34:00.496 --> 34:01.581
Welcome to the White House,
               ma'am.

34:02.248 --> 34:03.166
-Madam First Lady.
     -Welcome Madam First Lady.

34:04.083 --> 34:05.793
Good morning, Donald. I'm so,
     so sorry I'm late, Debbie.

34:06.669 --> 34:08.880
-I tend to run a little behind.
 -Let me show you to your office.

34:09.547 --> 34:12.675
Donald, so nice of you
    to greet me on my first day.

34:13.259 --> 34:14.177
-Betty Ford.
           -Good morning.

34:14.761 --> 34:15.762
You don't have to speak
             with them.

34:16.262 --> 34:16.929
What's your first day been like?

34:17.597 --> 34:19.057
Well, I don't know yet.
          I just got here.

34:19.682 --> 34:21.768
But it's all very exciting,
              isn't it?

34:22.268 --> 34:23.019
Just keep walking, ma'am.

34:23.728 --> 34:24.604
What's your opinion on whether
            your husband

34:25.104 --> 34:25.813
will pardon President Nixon?

34:26.397 --> 34:27.565
"No comment."
        "No comment" is fine.

34:28.107 --> 34:30.860
I know my husband,
          or the president,

34:31.277 --> 34:32.904
is eager to move forward

34:33.404 --> 34:34.739
with his new administration,

34:35.573 --> 34:39.911
and which I'm sure will be very
      different from the last.

34:40.411 --> 34:41.245
Right this way, ma'am.

34:41.788 --> 34:42.830
Your office is through
            these doors.

34:43.289 --> 34:43.831
Mrs. Ford--

34:44.415 --> 34:45.166
One last question.

34:45.792 --> 34:47.460
Do you'll know
     if he'll pardon or convict?

34:48.711 --> 34:53.091
I'm confident the president
      will do the right thing.

34:53.591 --> 34:54.967
Now, if you'll excuse me.

34:55.802 --> 34:57.637
-Thanks, ladies and gentlemen.
 -One more question.

34:58.262 --> 35:00.139
Thank you,
      Mr. Rumsfeld. Thank you.

35:05.311 --> 35:07.313
-Here we are.

35:08.439 --> 35:10.399
I do apologize
     for the state of the room.

35:11.275 --> 35:14.278
Uh, we had to turn things around
           rather quickly.

35:14.487 --> 35:15.571
Yeah.

35:16.781 --> 35:19.325
I suppose I have some
    decorating to do. 

35:20.159 --> 35:22.870
Mm-hmm. Uh, this is your
          schedule, ma'am.

35:23.287 --> 35:23.871
Oh.

35:24.580 --> 35:26.499
I'll see you shortly
       for the staff meeting.

35:26.791 --> 35:27.834
Oh, Debbie.

35:28.584 --> 35:29.961
Um, could you tell me
    where my husband's office is?

35:30.628 --> 35:32.797
I'd love to stop in
           and say hello.

35:33.339 --> 35:34.632
The president has
       a full schedule today.

35:35.299 --> 35:37.844
-Oh, I see. Well--
      -Is there anything else?

35:38.511 --> 35:40.346
No. Thank you.

36:48.706 --> 36:51.959
Oh! Oh, dear, I--

36:52.585 --> 36:56.964
Oh, I hope I didn't keep
      you waiting too long. I--

36:57.590 --> 37:00.092
I'm still getting my bearing--
          I'm so sorry. I--

37:00.718 --> 37:03.554
As I was telling Debbie
           earlier, I'm--

37:04.555 --> 37:06.933
-Anyway, hello.
           -Hello.

37:07.600 --> 37:09.936
Everyone, the First Lady
        of the United States.

37:10.519 --> 37:12.438
-Welcome.

37:13.564 --> 37:14.649
So wonderful.

37:18.694 --> 37:21.155
I was just informing
         the staff that, uh,

37:21.864 --> 37:25.284
because of the unusual
       and last-minute nature

37:25.785 --> 37:26.619
of you becoming First Lady,

37:27.578 --> 37:29.789
we'd probably be canceling
     the upcoming State Dinner.

37:30.456 --> 37:32.792
Oh.
   I don't think that's necessary.

37:33.292 --> 37:34.210
Everyone completely understands.

37:35.086 --> 37:38.005
Well, on the contrary, I love
   a good dinner party. 

37:38.589 --> 37:40.758
The bigger the better.

37:41.926 --> 37:45.012
And if you'd like to do
          what you've done

37:45.888 --> 37:49.642
for the Nixon's State Dinners,
     that would be fine with me.

37:50.101 --> 37:52.687
We don't really have time

37:53.271 --> 37:55.523
to do what we've always done.

37:55.898 --> 37:57.316
Not with three days.

37:57.900 --> 37:59.026
I see.

37:59.652 --> 38:00.903
Ma'am.

38:01.404 --> 38:03.197
If I may be so bold,

38:03.781 --> 38:06.117
surely the president,
          surely everyone,

38:06.659 --> 38:09.787
would understand
       if you had to postpone.

38:10.830 --> 38:13.040
Everyone knows
      how this whole situation

38:13.666 --> 38:16.544
has been sprung on you,
         even King Hussein.

38:16.919 --> 38:18.004
Are you sure? It--

38:18.629 --> 38:21.382
It seems awfully last minute
             to cancel.

38:22.008 --> 38:25.303
Not at all.
   It's completely understandable.

38:28.973 --> 38:34.520
Well then,
   I suppose that's what we'll do.

39:11.557 --> 39:12.433
-Oh, my gosh!
                -Oh!

39:13.059 --> 39:16.937
Betty? I'm sorry.
    Excuse me, Madam First Lady.

39:17.063 --> 39:17.980
Nancy.

39:18.522 --> 39:20.066
-Yeah. Nancy Howe.
            -Nancy Howe!

39:20.858 --> 39:23.110
The last time I saw you was
    at that dreadful PTA meeting.

39:23.694 --> 39:25.863
And that woman
         was talking about--

39:26.489 --> 39:27.365
-The history of education...

39:28.199 --> 39:30.493
-...in pre-colonial Virginia.
   -I thought it would never end.

39:31.077 --> 39:33.913
Three hours seared
           into my brain.

39:39.585 --> 39:41.504
It's so nice to know
            you're here.

39:42.088 --> 39:45.800
An actual person that I know
              and like.

39:46.092 --> 39:47.176
Yeah.

39:47.593 --> 39:48.594
Hmm?

39:49.428 --> 39:51.514
Take it. It's on the house.

39:52.056 --> 39:53.099
Thank you.

39:53.933 --> 39:56.894
Hey, how's it going? Are the
     aides overwhelming you yet?

39:58.771 --> 39:59.730
Not yet.

40:01.774 --> 40:02.650
And thanks for this.

40:03.067 --> 40:04.527
Don't tell anyone.

40:05.903 --> 40:06.737
Oh.

40:07.696 --> 40:11.867
Uh, do you by chance know
    how I get back to my office?

40:12.868 --> 40:14.120
I do.

40:14.912 --> 40:15.663
Mm-hmm, yeah.

40:16.539 --> 40:21.043
It's hard to believe that just
              last week

40:21.544 --> 40:22.795
this was Pat's office,

40:23.129 --> 40:24.213
and now she's...

40:24.797 --> 40:27.133
Helping her husband pack
             for prison.

40:32.430 --> 40:33.389
It does seem likely, doesn't it?

40:34.098 --> 40:36.976
He said he wasn't a crook,
      turns out he is a crook.

40:37.435 --> 40:38.811
Crooks go to jail.

40:41.439 --> 40:44.150
So what's the first First Lady
     thing they have you doing?

40:44.942 --> 40:48.487
Well, there was a State Dinner,
        but I'm canceling it.

40:49.280 --> 40:50.072
What? No, you're not.

40:50.656 --> 40:52.992
It was supposed to be three days
              from now

40:53.617 --> 40:56.162
and, well, my secretary said it
              was fine.

40:56.787 --> 41:00.291
No, no, no, no, no.
      You can't do that, Betty.

41:00.958 --> 41:03.961
No, it was actually
     my secretary's idea, so...

41:04.587 --> 41:05.671
Well, I don't care whose idea
               it was.

41:06.505 --> 41:08.299
This is your house.
         You get to decide.

41:08.924 --> 41:11.260
You really think
      one State Dinner matters?

41:11.969 --> 41:14.430
Let's see, did the Roosevelts
           showing support

41:14.972 --> 41:17.057
for every exiled
         European government

41:17.683 --> 41:20.019
after the Nazis took over
       their homeland matter?

41:20.644 --> 41:22.104
How about the Eisenhowers
           breaking bread

41:22.521 --> 41:23.481
with the Khrushchevs?

41:24.190 --> 41:27.234
The Nixons and the Brezhnevs
   may be the only cordial moment

41:27.818 --> 41:29.278
of this whole Cold War we're in.

41:29.695 --> 41:32.364
And maybe I'm biased

41:32.990 --> 41:34.575
because I spout out
         White House trivia

41:35.159 --> 41:36.285
in that gift shop all day long,

41:36.994 --> 41:39.538
but it seems to me like
        these are the moments

41:40.122 --> 41:41.916
that really, truly mattered.

41:42.875 --> 41:46.212
And they were State Dinners
   that First Ladies made happen.

41:47.671 --> 41:50.716
You just-- You-- You can't
   cancel your first State Dinner.

41:51.550 --> 41:54.720
This is your chance
      to start making history.

41:58.349 --> 42:00.726
-You wanted to see me, ma'am?
    -Oh! Yes, thank you.

42:01.018 --> 42:02.228
Please come in.

42:07.733 --> 42:09.860
How do you like
   what I've done with the place?

42:13.197 --> 42:14.031
Um.

42:14.573 --> 42:15.950
It's a joke, Debbie.

42:16.909 --> 42:17.952
-About the State Dinner,

42:18.911 --> 42:21.872
you'll be happy to know that
     I've decided not to cancel.

42:23.999 --> 42:26.043
-What?
      -I've come up with a plan

42:26.669 --> 42:29.088
I think you'll agree
           is very doable.

42:29.713 --> 42:31.340
Marrying some of
       Mrs. Nixon's traditions

42:32.049 --> 42:37.263
with my less formal,
     but no less festive, ideas.

42:41.058 --> 42:44.061
Oh... barbecue.

42:44.603 --> 42:46.772
Doesn't that sound fun?

42:47.690 --> 42:49.733
Be sure to let everyone know

42:50.276 --> 42:52.236
the president
        is counting on this.

42:52.861 --> 42:55.281
He's even more excited
             than I am.

42:57.616 --> 42:58.951
Thank you, Debbie.

43:01.245 --> 43:02.788
Thank you, ma'am.

43:10.296 --> 43:12.131
Good morning.
       Thanks for being with us.

43:12.631 --> 43:13.299
Monday, the 12th of January.

43:13.924 --> 43:14.800
Just eight days until
          the inauguration,

43:15.634 --> 43:16.302
the new administration,
           new president.

43:16.969 --> 43:17.803
Everybody's trying to get
           an angle here.

43:18.637 --> 43:20.598
Absolutely.
    A lot going on this morning.

43:24.602 --> 43:25.352
-Can I get you anything else?
                -No.

43:25.936 --> 43:27.771
-We're fine, thank you.
               -Okay.

43:30.232 --> 43:31.400
-Too bridal?
                -No.

43:32.276 --> 43:34.069
No. I see "hope" and "glory."

43:34.653 --> 43:35.696
-I see "elegance..."

43:36.280 --> 43:37.364
..."timeless" and "victorious."

43:37.948 --> 43:40.618
Oh, Jason is a genius,

43:41.160 --> 43:43.287
and you look exquisite.

43:43.829 --> 43:44.955
-I love you, Mel.

43:45.331 --> 43:47.666
I love you too. Come in.

43:50.669 --> 43:53.005
-Valerie, you're here.

43:53.672 --> 43:54.340
Girl, that dress...

43:54.965 --> 43:56.300
-Careful, Mrs. Obama.
               -Okay.

44:00.471 --> 44:02.973
-Hmm? Hmm?
                -Wow.

44:04.475 --> 44:05.476
Can we talk for a minute?

44:06.101 --> 44:07.227
Could you all give us
           a few minutes?

44:07.936 --> 44:10.147
-Yeah, sure.
     -I promise I'll be careful.

44:11.148 --> 44:13.692
Thanks, ladies. 

44:20.866 --> 44:22.868
-So beautiful.
                -Oh.

44:23.702 --> 44:25.496
But that's not why you're here.

44:25.996 --> 44:27.956
Rahm thought we should talk.

44:28.957 --> 44:31.168
Rahm wants. Rahm feels.
            Rahm thought.

44:31.669 --> 44:32.544
He just simply suggested

44:33.337 --> 44:35.714
that I be the liaison between
     the East Wing and the West.

44:36.340 --> 44:38.550
Great. So how do I get Rahm
            to understand

44:39.176 --> 44:40.636
that I'm not here
     to be a glorified hostess?

44:41.345 --> 44:45.182
Michelle, we want to ease you
         into complex areas.

44:45.724 --> 44:47.101
Val? Hello?

44:47.518 --> 44:48.602
-Hello?

44:49.186 --> 44:50.229
You sound just like them
             right now.

44:50.854 --> 44:52.439
-Michelle...
     -Fashion shoots? Gardening?

44:53.023 --> 44:54.274
You want me to be roasted alive

44:54.817 --> 44:57.152
as being elitist
          and out of touch?

44:58.696 --> 45:01.156
Valerie. You're my friend.

45:01.907 --> 45:03.117
You know what I can do.

45:03.575 --> 45:05.202
It's complicated right now.

45:06.370 --> 45:10.040
We, of all people,
 we can't rock the boat too much.

45:12.042 --> 45:14.002
Yeah. I know.

45:24.763 --> 45:26.181
-Morning, Mom.
              -Mm-hmm.

45:26.765 --> 45:28.684
I was talking garden
            all morning.

45:29.268 --> 45:32.855
Nothing like a curly kale
            master class.

45:33.063 --> 45:34.106
Hmm.

45:37.526 --> 45:39.069
I'm gonna need help.

45:40.279 --> 45:41.363
Can you stay here?

45:42.072 --> 45:45.200
The girls are gonna need
   some stability and continuity.

45:45.784 --> 45:46.493
They're gonna need their grandma

45:47.077 --> 45:48.996
to keep their feet
           on the ground.

45:49.580 --> 45:51.039
The girls need me?

45:55.377 --> 45:58.464
You need me. Hmm.

46:02.926 --> 46:04.970
Then I am here.

46:11.769 --> 46:14.104
-Mommy.

46:14.313 --> 46:16.482
Mom. Mama.

46:20.068 --> 46:21.195
Rahm?

46:21.570 --> 46:22.446
Madam First Lady.

46:22.946 --> 46:24.114
How's it all going?

46:25.282 --> 46:28.160
I have 87 pages to go through
          in the next hour.

46:28.619 --> 46:29.536
Why are you sidelining me?

46:30.162 --> 46:31.747
Can you guys give us
          a minute, please?

46:32.456 --> 46:34.416
-Give us a few minutes. Thanks.
          -Of course.

46:34.917 --> 46:36.502
-Ma'am.
            -First Lady.

46:38.420 --> 46:40.672
I'm trying to ensure
         that the East Wing

46:41.298 --> 46:42.508
compliments our agenda
          in the West Wing.

46:43.300 --> 46:45.803
So you turned me into a fluffy,
      inconsequential hostess.

46:46.470 --> 46:48.347
-No one's gonna buy it.
       -Well, that's the job.

46:48.847 --> 46:50.140
It doesn't have to be.

46:53.101 --> 46:55.687
Do you really think--
    Be honest with me, all right?

46:56.480 --> 47:00.025
You really think working on the
     board of a Chicago hospital

47:00.859 --> 47:02.194
has anything at all to do
            with creating

47:03.153 --> 47:05.989
a countrywide health care system
    for 200 million-plus people?

47:06.824 --> 47:07.658
I'm saying
       that I can contribute.

47:08.283 --> 47:09.368
And I'm saying,
        with all due respect,

47:09.993 --> 47:10.702
-that you're not qualified.
             -Excuse me?

47:11.328 --> 47:12.454
I don't want you to become
             a liability

47:12.996 --> 47:13.705
to your husband is all.

47:14.331 --> 47:15.290
But you were more than happy
           to pimp me out

47:15.666 --> 47:16.458
during the campaign.

47:17.042 --> 47:18.252
The campaign is over.
          This is politics

47:18.836 --> 47:19.461
and the business of government.

47:20.003 --> 47:20.879
-You're a real--
               -What?

47:21.672 --> 47:23.966
What am I "real"? An asshole?
       A pit bull? A jerk-off?

47:24.550 --> 47:26.510
A condescending,
        patronizing monster?

47:27.052 --> 47:29.888
I was gonna say a "charmer."

47:33.183 --> 47:34.226
You know what?
      You wanna make an omelet,

47:34.685 --> 47:35.310
you gotta break some eggs.

47:35.894 --> 47:37.396
And I don't care
          about any of that

47:37.896 --> 47:38.981
other peripheral bullshit.

47:39.565 --> 47:40.691
-You should.
        -Caring isn't my job.

47:41.233 --> 47:42.359
Absolute loyalty
         to your husband is.

47:43.360 --> 47:45.654
Being the bad guy so he doesn't
    have to be, that's my focus.

47:46.363 --> 47:47.698
I will body check anyone
    who gets in the way of that.

47:48.323 --> 47:50.284
-Even me?
     -If you become an obstacle.

47:51.410 --> 47:53.287
-You're a smart woman.
        -Oh, thank you, Rahm.

47:53.871 --> 47:55.247
So, I'm not gonna patronize you,

47:55.706 --> 47:56.540
but the fact that you're not

47:57.165 --> 48:00.294
a qualified career politician
             is a fact.

48:00.878 --> 48:01.712
It's not sexist or racist.

48:02.379 --> 48:03.338
So, please, I'm begging you,
         don't turn me into

48:03.922 --> 48:04.798
some kind of
        cliché villain here.

48:05.507 --> 48:07.050
All right? We've known
     each other a long time now.

48:07.593 --> 48:08.635
Amy and I have been
           to your house.

48:09.344 --> 48:11.096
So I'm pretty certain,
       Michelle-- Mrs. Obama,

48:11.889 --> 48:13.765
that we can find a process
             that works.

48:14.558 --> 48:17.477
If I'm willing to roll over
    and become a Stepford FLOTUS.

48:18.061 --> 48:19.605
Not happening. Also, Gwen's out.

48:20.230 --> 48:21.648
Oh, my God.
    We already went through this.

48:22.232 --> 48:23.275
Letting you foist
          a chief of staff

48:23.734 --> 48:24.610
on me was my first mistake.

48:25.235 --> 48:26.320
You're opening
        a can of worms here.

48:27.237 --> 48:30.365
No. I'm accepting your position
       and stepping into mine.

48:30.741 --> 48:31.783
Gwen will be replaced.

48:32.576 --> 48:35.787
I'll pick my team, choose my
     causes. You leave me alone.

48:36.246 --> 48:37.247
Understood?

48:42.461 --> 48:43.587
Madam First Lady.

48:44.463 --> 48:45.923
Rahm.

48:58.226 --> 48:59.853
Honey, I'm home. 

49:00.312 --> 49:02.105
A nutritious meal

49:02.940 --> 49:04.858
from the future
         White House garden.

49:05.484 --> 49:10.489
Prepared by the horticulturist
            to the stars.

49:10.948 --> 49:12.783
Oh, boy. 

49:13.450 --> 49:16.870
You've been misused
            Talk to me...

49:17.329 --> 49:18.747
You seem nervous.

49:19.164 --> 49:20.874
Huh? Me? No. Not at all.

49:21.500 --> 49:23.085
I mean, y-you managed to make
           romaine lettuce

49:23.669 --> 49:26.338
seem threatening,
          but... 

49:27.130 --> 49:28.966
What you need...

49:29.466 --> 49:30.717
Look, uh...

49:31.176 --> 49:32.135
What you want...

49:32.678 --> 49:34.888
Rahm told me
       that you and he spoke.

49:35.472 --> 49:38.767
We did.
      It was real illuminating.

49:39.351 --> 49:42.104
Hmm. Mm-hmm.
       He said the same thing.

49:42.312 --> 49:42.771
Mm-hmm.

49:43.355 --> 49:45.148
All the time that you spent

49:46.316 --> 49:49.444
She had other men
          throw you outdoors

49:49.653 --> 49:50.612
Uh, look.

49:51.196 --> 49:54.116
-R-Rahm thinks--
         -Stop right there.

49:55.200 --> 49:58.704
You tell your work wife
        that your actual wife

49:59.329 --> 50:02.541
said to stay out of our
          family business.

50:03.041 --> 50:04.835
Got it.
        Now I have two wives

50:05.502 --> 50:06.878
and neither of them are happy.

50:07.504 --> 50:10.382
I'll make everything
              all right

50:16.722 --> 50:18.348
You are my number one.

50:18.557 --> 50:19.349
Mm-hmm.

50:19.808 --> 50:20.600
-My main wife.
              -Mm-hmm.

50:21.143 --> 50:21.935
And he's a distant second.

50:22.644 --> 50:24.521
For a start, he can't kiss
         as well as you can.

50:25.063 --> 50:26.064
He-- He's working on it.

50:26.565 --> 50:27.315
But he's, uh-- 

50:28.233 --> 50:30.318
--He hasn't got it quite yet.

50:32.029 --> 50:34.322
Can I eat now?

50:34.531 --> 50:35.490
Mm-hmm.

50:36.491 --> 50:38.076
Can I get a little meat in here,
    or I haven't earned my meat--

50:38.702 --> 50:40.912
There's no meat
     in the White House garden.

50:41.538 --> 50:43.165
-I'm going to try it out.

50:44.166 --> 50:46.752
Oh, don't let them say I didn't
   try it. All right. Here we go.

50:49.546 --> 50:51.715
Mm-hmm! Mmm! Organic!

50:52.215 --> 50:53.550
-Mmm.
             -I approve!

50:55.552 --> 50:57.471
This is-- This has got the
   presidential seal of approval!

51:03.685 --> 51:05.771
I let Rahm
       pick my chief of staff.

51:06.229 --> 51:07.606
That was my mistake.

51:08.440 --> 51:11.526
That's why I asked you here.

51:14.404 --> 51:17.074
I want you to be
         my chief of staff.

51:20.786 --> 51:22.120
Gwen didn't work out.

51:22.621 --> 51:23.789
I need someone who knows me.

51:24.414 --> 51:26.416
Someone who understands
           my priorities.

51:27.375 --> 51:29.377
You've been in the trenches
        with me. I trust you.

51:31.922 --> 51:33.632
Michelle, I'm flattered.

51:35.217 --> 51:36.927
But I was only supposed to be
    here for a few months to work

51:37.552 --> 51:38.845
-on the inauguration committee.
              -I know.

51:39.554 --> 51:41.723
And Neil already
     doesn't love me being away.

51:42.099 --> 51:43.141
I know.

51:43.642 --> 51:46.103
But husbands can relocate.

51:47.104 --> 51:47.813
And remember what you told me

51:48.438 --> 51:50.774
when Barack was still
          in the primaries?

51:53.110 --> 51:55.320
That you should start embracing
              the fact

51:56.154 --> 51:59.324
that your life might change
           in a huge way.

52:00.325 --> 52:02.452
And I remember what else
            you told me.

52:03.411 --> 52:07.290
About being open to exciting,
      unexpected new horizons.

52:08.166 --> 52:10.293
I can be so inspirational
     when I want to be, can't I?

52:11.128 --> 52:12.629
Susan,
     let's kick some fucking ass

52:13.171 --> 52:15.090
the way we did back in Chicago.

52:15.799 --> 52:19.427
You know what this means, right?
         You to be my boss.

52:28.687 --> 52:32.607
I really hope Neil
        likes Washington DC.

52:34.484 --> 52:36.153
Yes, yes!

52:36.987 --> 52:38.071
-Yes, yes!

52:38.530 --> 52:39.948
-Aw!

52:40.365 --> 52:41.324
Oh!

52:41.658 --> 52:42.868
Yeah. Okay.

52:43.451 --> 52:45.370
-Okay!
       -Mm-hmm. You promised.

52:46.371 --> 52:48.206
-Hmm.
          -Okay.

52:49.833 --> 52:51.334
Where do we start?

53:06.224 --> 53:07.934
That would be lovely.
         I would love that.

53:08.393 --> 53:09.519
It would be lovely.

53:09.895 --> 53:10.979
We have, uh, the Dead Sea,

53:11.646 --> 53:12.939
-and you don't sink, you float.
             -Excuse me.

53:13.523 --> 53:15.317
-So, it is very beautiful.

53:16.193 --> 53:21.406
Ladies and gentlemen,
   it has been our great pleasure

53:22.407 --> 53:23.825
spending a wonderful evening

53:24.492 --> 53:27.495
with our new friends,
    King Hussein and Queen Alia,

53:28.413 --> 53:30.749
here at the White House
     for our first State Dinner.

53:37.756 --> 53:39.799
And it is my great pleasure

53:40.926 --> 53:46.264
to ask the most beautiful woman
           in the world...

53:48.225 --> 53:51.603
if she'll dance our first State
        Dinner dance with me.

53:52.062 --> 53:53.772
-Oh.

54:10.455 --> 54:11.748
I miss dancing with you.

54:12.749 --> 54:16.753
I'll dance with you anytime,
           Mr. President.

54:17.921 --> 54:20.799
-I like the sound of that.
       -Mmm. I'm sure you do.

54:29.474 --> 54:31.518
I'm so impressed with you.

54:32.727 --> 54:35.438
Pulling this all together
        on such short notice.

54:37.274 --> 54:38.858
I'm impressed with you, Jerry.

54:39.484 --> 54:42.570
You have a lot
    on your shoulders right now.
